        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Homologous series have same ____ group and differ by ____ unit.</text>
            <option id="A">Functional , -CH2-</option><option id="B">Alkyl, -CH3</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Same chemical properties, gradual change in physical properties.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Compounds with same molecular formula but different structures are ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Isomers</option><option id="B">Homologs</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Basis of structural complexity in organic chem.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Isomerism due to different arrangement of atoms in space is ____ isomerism.</text>
