            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Includes Geometrical and Optical.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Breaking of covalent bond such that each atom takes one electron is ____ fission.</text>
            <option id="A">Homolytic</option><option id="B">Heterolytic</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Forms free radicals.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Breaking of covalent bond such that one atom takes both electrons is ____ fission.</text>
            <option id="A">Heterolytic</option><option id="B">Homolytic</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Forms carbocations and carbanions.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Species with positive charge on carbon are ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Carbocations</option><option id="B">Carbanions</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Electrophiles, usually sp2 hybridized.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Species with negative charge on carbon are ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Carbanions</option><option id="B">Carbocations</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Nucleophiles, usually sp3 hybridized.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Electron-seeking species are called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Electrophiles</option><option id="B">Nucleophiles</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Examples: H+, NO2+, AlCl3.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Nucleus-seeking species are called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Nucleophiles</option><option id="B">Electrophiles</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Examples: OH-, NH3, Cl-.</explanation>
        </question>
        <question>
            <text>Permanent displacement of electrons along a chain due to presence of polar bond is ____ effect.</text>
